==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''yeoman'''  (''plural'' yeomen)
#an [[official]] providing honorable service in a [[royal]] or [[high noble]] [[household]]
#a yeoman is third in order of the feudal servant fighting classes below knight, squire and above a page. typically a mounted archer (as in Chaucer's Canterbury Tales Knight's Prologue).
#a [[Yeoman Warder]]
#a [[clerk]] in the [[US]] [[navy]]
#a member of the Yeomanry Cavalry officially chartered in 1794 originating around the 1760s.
#a member of the Imperial Yeomanry officially created in 1890s and renamed in 1907.
#(''British'') a [[former]] [[class]] small [[freeholder]]s who [[farm]] their own [[land]]
